This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it addresses the problem of 3D human pose estimation from single images using deep neural networks. It also involves the use of 2D pose estimation and image-to-3D pose mapping, which are common techniques in computer vision. 

The paper also involves the use of motion capture data, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. 

Additionally, the paper involves the use of efficient 3D pose retrieval, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the reconstruction of 3D pose, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
